games.name: Cincinnati Reds at Washington Nationals

headlines.description: Nick Senzel made a leaping catch against the right-field wall to save a run in the ninth inning, then hit a two-run homer leading off the 10th to lift the Cincinnati Reds over the Nationals 5-4 Thursday for their first series sweep at Washington...
headlines.shortLinkText: Senzel saves run in 9th, homers leading off 10th and Reds beat Nationals 5-4 for sweep

games.name: Oakland Athletics at Detroit Tigers

headlines.description: Javier Bez had a two-run single in the first inning, All-Star Michael Lorenzen combined with three relievers on a four-hitter and the Detroit Tigers routed to the Oakland Athletics 9-0 Thursday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bez's 2-run single in 1st starts Tigers to 9-0 rout of A's. 10th time Oakland shut out

games.name: Chicago Cubs at Milwaukee Brewers

headlines.description: Victor Caratini hit a tiebreaking home run off Michael Fulmer in the eighth inning, and the Milwaukee Brewers recovered from a blown three-run lead to beat the Chicago Cubs 6-5 Thursday and gain a split of their four-game series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Caratini 8th-inning homer lifts Brewers over Cubs 6-5, overcoming Bellinger's 4 hits, 3 RBIs

games.name: Toronto Blue Jays at Chicago White Sox

headlines.description: George Springer hit a tiebreaking RBI single during Toronto's six-run 11th inning, and the Blue Jays beat the Chicago White Sox 6-2 on Thursday in a doubleheader opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: George Springer gets key hit as Toronto Blue Jays beat Chicago White Sox 6-2 in 11 innings

games.name: Philadelphia Phillies at Tampa Bay Rays

headlines.description: Kyle Schwarber and Trea Turner had RBI singles in the 11th inning and the Philadelphia Phillies completed a three-game sweep of Tampa Bay with a 3-1 victory Thursday night that extended the Rays' losing streak to a season-high five.
headlines.shortLinkText: Schwarber, Turner lift Phillies to 3-1 win, send Rays to season-high 5th loss in row

games.name: St. Louis Cardinals at Miami Marlins

headlines.description: Jack Flaherty hoped to take control of Thursday's series finale against the Miami Marlins right away.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arenado homers, Cardinals pitchers blank Marlins to win 3-0 and avoid sweep

games.name: Baltimore Orioles at New York Yankees

headlines.description: Gunnar Hendersons best night of his brief big league career sent Luis Severino to one of his worst.
headlines.shortLinkText: Henderson's 2 homers, 4 hits, 5 RBIs lead Orioles to 14-1 rout of Yankees and Severino

headlines.description: For five innings, the Guardians managed just one paltry run. Jos Ramrez and Josh Naylor changed that with two swings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ramrez, Naylor homer on consecutive pitches in the Guardians' 6-1 win over the Royals

games.name: Texas Rangers at Boston Red Sox

headlines.description: Kik Hernndez blooped a bases-loaded, broken-bat single in the seventh to turn a one-run deficit into a one-run lead, and the Red Sox weren't done yet.
headlines.shortLinkText: Red Sox burst out for 6 in the 7th, beat the AL West-leading Rangers 10-6

games.name: Seattle Mariners at Houston Astros

headlines.description: Eugenio Surez homered twice with three RBI and J.P. Crawford added a solo shot to lead the Seattle Mariners to a 5-1 victory over the Houston Astros on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Surez hits 2 homers, Crawford has 1 as Mariners beat Astros 5-1

games.name: Toronto Blue Jays at Chicago White Sox

headlines.description: Whit Merrifield played every inning of Toronto's doubleheader on Thursday. It was a long day, but a very productive one.
headlines.shortLinkText: Whit Merrifield helps Toronto Blue Jays beat Chicago White Sox 5-4 for doubleheader sweep

games.name: New York Mets at Arizona Diamondbacks

headlines.description: New York starter Carlos Carrasco dominated for eight innings, setting the tone for the first shutout of the Arizona Diamondbacks in 89 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lindor homers and triples twice, Mets bash Diamondbacks 9-0 to win fifth straight

games.name: Pittsburgh Pirates at Los Angeles Dodgers

headlines.description: Max Muncy and Freddie Freeman homered and Julio Urias pitched six innings to help the Los Angeles Dodgers beat the Pittsburgh Pirates 5-2 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dodgers beat the Pirates 5-2 to pull within a half-game of AL West-leading Arizona
